Broken Symlink
-------------------
< set the file name with date suffix
  create current day backup file
  append text to the file >

FILENAME=backup-$(date +"%d-%m-%Y").obj
touch $FILENAME
echo "backup data..." >> $FILENAME

< create short link symlink to the file >

ln -s $FILENAME backup.obj

< create backup directory
  move short link to backup directory >

mkdir backups
mv backup.obj backups/

< ERROR the link is not relative
ll -l
...
lrwxrwxrwx 1 tammit tammit   21 Jun 22 16:46 backup.obj -> backup-22-06-2022.obj
...
>

REPLACE
ln -s $FILENAME backup.obj
WITH
ln -s ~/$FILENAME backup.obj




Binary Numbers
--------------
1.
    111 = 7,
    100 = 4,
    10110 = 22
2. 8 bits Binary represents:
    0 - 255 Decimal
3. 9 bits Binary to represent positive / negative 0-255 range
    1 bit sign (0 positive, 1 negative)
    8 bits 0 - 255
4. binary represenaion of floating point number
    4 bits - the integer part
    4 bits - the fractional part
    - in case of signed number
    1 bit sign (0 positive, 1 negative)
    4 bits - the integer part
    3 bits - the fractional part
